Copper alloy, probably bronze, cast, and gilt.

Copper alloy, probably bronze, cast, and gilt. The heavily cast putto balances the Tuscan column on top of his left leg and holds its top with his raised arm in his left hand. His right arm rests by his side, whilst his right foot is slightly raised, resting on his left ankle. His head is turned towards the left as he regards the column.
